<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1529,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1529,1555]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Palpus yellow. Coxa I yellow, coxae II and III (except narrow apex) blackish. All femora yellow. Hairs and bristles on head and thorax blackish. Cercus with outer process curved and spine-like apically. Hypandrium short and broad, with small trapezoid apical incision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1529,2036]" box="[197,1034,1649,1676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,341,1649,1675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Description</emphasis>
. Male. Body length 2.0– 
<quantity box="[636,728,1650,1676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[885,1029,1650,1676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.6">3.6–3.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1529,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on head blackish; postocular bristles (except uppermost bristle) yellowish. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 
<number box="[857,871,1730,1756]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
very long oc and 
<number box="[1099,1114,1730,1756]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
very short posterior hairs. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[267,337,1770,1796]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[152,1424,674,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,634,1759]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Chrysotimus curvispinus sp. nov., male. 5. Antenna (excluding scape and pedicel), lateral view; 6. genitalia, lateral view; 7. hypandrium, ventral view. Scale 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184634/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[322,337,1770,1796]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) black; pedicel with circlet of dark brown apical hairs; first flagellomere rather short, 
<number box="[1352,1389,1770,1796]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="0.8">0.8</number>
x as long as wide; arista dorsal, black, with very short pubescence. Proboscis brownish black, with black hairs; palpus yellow, with yellow hairs and 
<number box="[587,602,1850,1876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
yellow apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1529,2036]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,620]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on thorax blackish; 
<number box="[1175,1190,1890,1916]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="5.0">5</number>
strong dc, 
<number box="[1319,1363,1890,1916]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
irregularly paired acr short and hair-like; scutellum with 
<number box="[770,784,1930,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of bristles, outer pair slightly long, about 
<number box="[1352,1389,1930,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="0.4">0.4</number>
x as long as inner pair. Propleuron with 
<number box="[579,594,1970,1996]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="1.0">1</number>
yellowish hair and 
<number box="[834,848,1970,1996]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" value="1.0">1</number>
yellowish bristle on lower portion. Legs yellow; coxa I yellow, coxae II and III (except narrow apex) blackish; fore leg from tip of tibia onward brownish or brown; tarsi II and III from tip of tarsomere 
<number box="[666,681,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
onward brown. Hairs and bristles on legs black; coxae with pale hairs and bristles; coxa I with 
<number box="[505,520,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
long bristles. Femora II and III each with 
<number box="[1018,1033,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
av at apex. Tibia I apically with 
<number box="[1421,1436,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
short bristle; tibia II with 
<number box="[457,472,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
ad and 
<number box="[567,581,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
pd, apically with 
<number box="[797,812,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
bristles; tibia III with 
<number box="[1081,1096,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
ad and 
<number box="[1191,1206,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
pd, apically with 
<number box="[1421,1436,232,258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
bristles. Relative lengths of tibia and 
<number box="[589,603,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
tarsomeres of legs LI 
<number box="[868,904,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.7">1.7</number>
: 
<number box="[928,965,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.1">1.1</number>
: 
<number box="[988,1039,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.55">0.55</number>
: 
<number box="[1062,1099,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.4">0.4</number>
: 
<number box="[1122,1174,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.25">0.25</number>
: 
<number box="[1197,1252,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.25">0.25</number>
; LII 
<number box="[1309,1346,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="2.4">2.4</number>
: 
<number box="[1369,1420,272,298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.45">1.45</number>
: 
<number box="[151,188,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.6">0.6</number>
: 
<number box="[210,247,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.4">0.4</number>
: 
<number box="[270,321,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.25">0.25</number>
: 
<number box="[344,399,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.25">0.25</number>
; 
<collectionCode box="[411,458,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">LIII</collectionCode>
<number box="[466,503,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="2.6">2.6</number>
: 
<number box="[525,562,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.2">1.2</number>
: 
<number box="[585,622,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.7">0.7</number>
: 
<number box="[644,681,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.5">0.5</number>
: 
<number box="[704,740,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.3">0.3</number>
: 
<number box="[763,803,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.3">0.3</number>
. Wing nearly hyaline; veins brown, R 
<number box="[1247,1255,328,342]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1264,1271,328,342]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
and M nearly parallel apically; CuAx ratio 
<number box="[492,532,354,380]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="0.3">0.3</number>
. Squama brownish yellow with yellow hairs. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,620]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
Abdomen metallic green with pale gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on abdomen mostly blackish; tergum 
<number box="[151,166,434,460]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
with pale hairs and bristles. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[686,800,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[152,1424,674,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,634,1759]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Chrysotimus curvispinus sp. nov., male. 5. Antenna (excluding scape and pedicel), lateral view; 6. genitalia, lateral view; 7. hypandrium, ventral view. Scale 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184634/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
Figs. 
<number box="[752,800,434,460]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
</figureCitation>
): epandrium distinctly longer than wide, with 
<number box="[1341,1356,434,460]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
lateral bristle apically; surstylus not distinctly separated from epandrium, short and nearly acute apically; cercus rather long and narrow apically, with rather long outer process curved and spine-like apically; hypandrium short and broad, with small apical incision.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,620]" box="[197,993,594,620]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
Female. Body length 2.0 mm, wing length 
<quantity box="[700,793,594,620]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
. Similar to male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
