</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1842,2028]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,152,215]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,2002,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang and Yang, 2006" authorityName="Wang and Yang" authorityYear="2006" box="[809,1229,2002,2028]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcatus">
<emphasis box="[809,962,2002,2027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">C. bifurcatus</emphasis>
Wang and Yang, 
<number box="[1170,1229,2002,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</taxonomicName>
from Tibet in the shape of the first flagellomere and surstylus, but may be separated from the latter by the blackish mid and hind coxae. In 
<taxonomicName box="[265,417,189,214]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcatus">
<emphasis box="[265,417,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">C. bifurcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all coxae are yellow (Wang &amp; Yang, 
<number box="[864,928,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" value="2006.0">2006</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
